Ergo CEO Oletzky Apologizes for Sex Scandal, Bild Says

-- B y   C h r i s t i a n e   L e n z n e r
-- 
2011-06-10T08:54:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-10/ergo-ceo-oletzky-apologizes-for-sex-scandal-bild-says-correct-.html
(Corrects location in first paragraph.)  Ergo Versicherungsgruppe Chief
Executive Officer Torsten Oletzky apologized for a 2007
incentive party for sales agents that hosted prostitutes in
Budapest, Bild-Zeitung reported, citing an interview.  Oletzky said an internal investigation found the sex party
was a single incident, according to the interview.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christiane Lenzner at 
 clenzner@bloomberg.net  